    {
      "id": "intro-0",
      "sectionId": "intro",
      "title": "Intro",
      "body": "A cheatsheet for GnuPG, the encryption and signing software."
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-1",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Software",
      "body": "Gpg4win%20and%20the%20GPG%20Suite%20have%20OS-specific%20features.%0A%0A%E2%80%A2%20%5BGnuPG%5D(https%3A%2F%2Fgnupg.org%2F)%0A%E2%80%A2%20%5BGpg4win%5D(https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gpg4win.org%2F)%20(Windows)%0A%E2%80%A2%20%5BGPG%20Suite%5D(https%3A%2F%2Fgpgtools.org%2F)%20(macOS)%0A%0ASometimes%20GPG%20keys%20are%20referred%20as%20PGP%20keys.%20They're%20interchangeable%2C%20as%20they%20follow%20the%0A%5BOpenPGP%20Standard%5D(https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rfc-editor.org%2Frfc%2Frfc9580.html).",
      "encoded": true
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-4",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Create a key-pair",
      "body": "Generate your keys:\n\n```shell script\n$ gpg --generate-key\n\n```\n\n... or fully configure your keys.\n\n```shell script\n$ gpg --generate-full-keys\n```\n\n**Note:** Choose a strong passphrase! The encryption is only as strong as your passphrase."
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-8",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Key management",
      "body": "List your keys:\n\n```shell script\n$ gpg --list-keys\n\n```\n\nList your secret keys:\n\n```shell script\n$ gpg --list-secret-keys\n```\n\nExport your public key:\n\n```shell script\n$ gpg --export --armor <ID>\n\n```\n\nExport your secret key:\n\n```shell script\n$ gpg --export-secret-key --armor <ID>\n```\n\nDelete your public key:\n\n```shell script\n$ gpg --delete-key <ID>\n\n```\n\nDelete your secret key:\n\n```shell script\n$ gpg --delete-secret-key <ID>\n```"
    },
    {
      "id": "s2-17",
      "sectionId": "s2",
      "title": "Symmetric",
      "body": "Encrypt with a passphrase:\n\n```shell script\n$ gpg -c <FILE>\n\n```\n\nEncrypt as ASCII with `-a` flag:\n\n```shell script\n$ gpg -ac <FILE>\n```\n\nSet output file path with `-o` flag:\n\n```shell script\n$ gpg -c <FILE> -o <PATH>\n\n```\n\nDecrypt with a passphrase:\n\n```shell script\n$ gpg <FILE>\n```\n\n**Note:** Choose a strong passphrase! The encryption is only as strong as your passphrase."
    },
    {
      "id": "s2-24",
      "sectionId": "s2",
      "title": "Asymmetric",
      "body": "Encrypt%20using%20public-private%20key%20encryption%3A%0A%0A%60%60%60shell%20script%0A%24%20gpg%20-e%20-r%20%3CRECIPIENT%3E%20%3CFILE%3E%0A%0A%60%60%60%0A%0AEncrypt%20as%20ASCII%20output%20with%20%60-a%60%20flag%3A%0A%0A%60%60%60shell%20script%0A%24%20gpg%20-ea%20-r%20%3CRECIPIENT%3E%20%3CFILE%3E%0A%60%60%60%0A%0AEncrypt%20and%20sign%20with%20%60-s%60%20flag%3A%0A%0A%60%60%60shell%20script%0A%24%20gpg%20-se%20-r%20%3CRECIPIENT%3E%20%3CFILE%3E%0A%0A%60%60%60%0A%0AAdd%20multiple%20recipients%3A%0A%0A%60%60%60shell%20script%0A%24%20gpg%20-e%20-r%20%3CRECIPIENT1%3E%20-r%20%3CRECIPIENT2%3E%20%3CFILE%3E%0A%60%60%60%0A%0ASet%20output%20file%20path%20with%20%60-o%60%20flag%3A%0A%0A%60%60%60shell%20script%0A%24%20gpg%20-e%20-o%20%3CPATH%3E%20-r%20%3CRECIPIENT%3E%20%3CFILE%3E%0A%0A%60%60%60%0A%0ADecrypt%20with%20your%20private%20key%3A%0A%0A%60%60%60shell%20script%0A%24%20gpg%20%3CFILE%3E%0A%60%60%60%0A%0AReplace%20%60%3CRECIPIENT%3E%60%20with%20your%20intended%20recipient's%20%5Bimported%20public%20key%5D(%23importing-a-public-key)%20ID.",
      "encoded": true
    },
    {
      "id": "s2-34",
      "sectionId": "s2",
      "title": "Importing%20a%20public%20key",
      "body": "Import%20using%20a%20file%3A%0A%0A%60%60%60shell%20script%0A%24%20gpg%20--import%20%3CFILE%3E%0A%0A%60%60%60%0A%0AImport%20using%20a%20link%20(macOS%2FLinux)%3A%0A%0A%60%60%60shell%20script%0A%24%20curl%20%3CWEBSITE%3E%20%7C%20gpg%20--import%0A%60%60%60%0A%0ADon't%20forget%20to%20sign%20the%20imported%20key%3A%0A%0A%60%60%60shell%20script%0A%24%20gpg%20--sign-key%20%3CID%3E%0A%0A%60%60%60%0A%0A%23%23%20Commit%20Signing%0A%0A%23%23%23%20Local%20Git%20Setup%0A%0AEnable%20GPG%20signing%3A%0A%0A%60%60%60shell%20script%0A%24%20git%20config%20--global%20commit.gpgsign%20true%0A%60%60%60%0A%0ASet%20the%20signing%20key%3A%0A%0A%60%60%60shell%20script%0A%24%20git%20config%20--global%20user.signingkey%20%3CID%3E%0A%0A%60%60%60%0A%0ASet%20location%20of%20GPG%3A%0A%0A%60%60%60shell%20script%0A%24%20git%20config%20--global%20gpg.program%20%3CPROGRAM%3E%0A%60%60%60%0A%0A**Note%3A**%20Your%20name%20and%20email%20must%20match%20on%20Git%20and%20GnuPG.",
      "encoded": true
    },
    {
      "id": "s2-44",
      "sectionId": "s2",
      "title": "GPG Program List",
      "body": "Replace `<PROGRAM>` with one of the following:\n\n| Platform    | Value                                      |\n| ----------- | ------------------------------------------ |\n| Windows     | `C:\\Program Files (x86)\\GnuPG\\bin\\gpg.exe` |\n| macOS/Linux | /usr/local/bin/gpg                         |"
    },
    {
      "id": "s2-46",
      "sectionId": "s2",
      "title": "Exporting%20your%20public%20key",
      "body": "Export%20as%20ASCII%3A%0A%0A%60%60%60shell%20script%0A%24%20gpg%20--export%20--armor%20%3CID%3E%0A%0A%60%60%60%0A%0A**Note%3A**%20Platforms%2C%20like%20GitHub%2C%20may%20ask%20you%20to%20verify%20the%20email%20you%20set%20in%20Git%20and%20GnuPG.%0A%0A%23%23%20Windows%3A%20Add%20to%20Startup%20Apps%20%7B.cols-1%7D%0A%0A%23%23%23%20PowerShell%20Commands%0A%0AWhen%20you%20do%20a%20full%20restart%2C%20the%20GPG%20agent%20might%20not%20automatically%20start.%20Add%20the%20GnuPG's%20IPC%20tool%20to%20Startup%20Apps%20using%0APowerShell%3A%0A%0A%60%60%60shell%20script%0A%24%20%24shell%20%3D%20New-Object%20-ComObject%20WScript.Shell%0A%24%20%24shortcut%20%3D%20%24shell.CreateShortcut(%22C%3A%5CUsers%5C%24(%24Env%3AUserName)%5CAppData%5CRoaming%5CMicrosoft%5CWindows%5CStart%20Menu%5CPrograms%5CStartup%5Cgpg-connect-agent.lnk%22)%0A%24%20%24shortcut.TargetPath%20%3D%20%22C%3A%5CProgram%20Files%20(x86)%5CGnuPG%5Cbin%5Cgpg-connect-agent.exe%22%0A%24%20%24shortcut.Arguments%20%3D%20%22%2Fbye%22%0A%24%20%24shortcut.Save()%0A%60%60%60%0A%0AStart%20up%20manually%20instead%3A%0A%0A%60%60%60shell%20script%0A%24%20gpgconf%20--launch%20gpg-agent%0A%0A%60%60%60%0A%0ACheck%20if%20it%20was%20successfully%20added%20%5Bhere%5D(ms-settings%3Astartupapps).%0A%0A%60%60%60",
      "encoded": true
    }
